    "body": "Problem:  Mixing \"buf\" and \"M.bufs.msg\" in M.msg:start_timer().\r\nSolution: Replace \"M.bufs.msg\" with \"buf\".\r\n\r\nFix #38599 ",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-30T16:36:45Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38600#discussion_r3009316102"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/38600"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3009316102"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Consider adding a regression test for this bug scenario in the existing ui2 functional suite (e.g. `test/functional/ui/messages2_spec.lua`): start a msg-window timeout, then change `require('vim._core.ui2').bufs.msg` (or otherwise cause the module’s msg buffer reference to differ) before the timer fires, and assert the timer still removes the expected empty line from the original buffer. This would prevent future reintroduction of the inconsistent-buffer read in the timer callback.",
            "commit_id": "a4cfb46f7a34bddc9bf98684ea6a08a41c81ce61",
            "created_at": "2026-03-30T11:54:26Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -67,7 +67,7 @@ function M.msg:start_timer(buf, id)\n \n     -- Remove message (including potentially leftover empty line).\n     api.nvim_buf_set_text(buf, mark[1], mark[2], mark[3].end_row, mark[3].end_col, {})\n-    if api.nvim_buf_get_lines(ui.bufs.msg, mark[1], mark[1] + 1, false)[1] == '' then\n+    if api.nvim_buf_get_lines(buf, mark[1], mark[1] + 1, false)[1] == '' then",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38600#discussion_r3009316102",
